{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f7726ed1-7f39-488f-ae53-5e84e20e6323","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four support a reason string. The skipped tests will appear as \"not executed\" / \"skipped\" in test results rather than silently disappearing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"03756024-7d46-4d77-9039-3cff09e3ffc8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax for skipping tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide this from my knowledge.","outputTokens":236,"requestId":"4C11:2F058A:DBBC31:111FA4E:6A012D80"},"id":"c7fba9ff-1d4e-441d-92f0-08bb61fed8fe","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:14:46.323Z","parentId":"030bd991-999b-4a06-9fc5-a21eda3e0a29"}
